pageContext.claim: “Now I hear that these same people that failed to get me in Washington have sent every piece of information to New York so that they can try to get me there.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence that the Mueller prosecutors passed information to Manhattan District Attorney Cyrus Vance Jr. (D), who is looking into payoffs made in 2016 to women who alleged they had affairs with Trump. (Mueller never sought charges against Trump regarding the payoffs.) Vance’s recent filings suggest that his probe may have expanded to cover other financial dealings at Trump's company.
